transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Hi, this is Viagra.

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: How are we doing, sir?

Speaker 2: Okay. I'm trying to cancel any future prescriptions being sent to me.

Speaker 1: Mr. Ronald?

Speaker 2: Yes.

Speaker 1: Any health concerns, or you just don't need it for a while? You want to hold it as needed? You have a lot left.

Speaker 2: I don't want any more. Period. I want it canceled.

Speaker 1: Okay. Yeah. I was asking because they offer you to pause so you can keep your price and reorder it.

Speaker 2: They don't have to pay a new doctor consultation.

Speaker 1: But if you want, I can cancel the one they finance for you.

Speaker 2: The only thing, if anything changes in the future, your price will be higher, obviously, because they're going to have to reinvest for a new doctor.

Speaker 1: That's fine. Your product doesn't work, so I want it canceled. I don't want any more ties.

Speaker 2: Okay. Yeah. I wish you would have told us that before so we would have given you something better.

Speaker 1: But I cancel everything for you here.

Speaker 2: Usually, it's better to communicate your issues so we can fix it, offer you a better solution, a better fit.

Speaker 1: But when we don't know, we can help, sir.

Speaker 2: Well, I called and talked to people two deliveries ago and told them to cancel.

Speaker 1: I just got a new prescription in the mail. I want it canceled.

Speaker 2: Everything will be canceled, sir. Fully canceled. You're fully canceled here already.

Speaker 1: I cancel everything for you.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Nothing to worry about, okay?

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: You're all set.

Speaker 2: Thank you.

Speaker 1: Bye-bye.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.
